Host-side QEMU pointer regression timeline, 2026-07-21

All graphical QEMU tests delivered keyboard input but not usable guest pointer
input. The released live ISO and qcow2 behaved the same, so this is not an
Azure Linux image-format or package-base difference.

Nearby Rawhide changes:
  2026-07-16
    kernel: 7.2.0-0.rc2 -> 7.2.0-0.rc3
    mutter: 51~alpha-1 -> 51~alpha-2
    PipeWire: updated to 1.6.8-2
  2026-07-17
    QEMU 11.0.0-11 installed
  2026-07-20
    bluez: 5.87-2 -> 5.87-4
    Wayland: 1.25.0 -> 1.26.0
    Mesa: 26.1.4 -> 26.1.5
    GLib and IBus also updated

BlueZ:
  The 5.87-4 changelog says it was updated to upstream HEAD "to fix a number
  of possible crashes." The journal has repeated Bluetooth headset profile
  connect/disconnect failures. There is no retained BlueZ coredump.

GNOME Shell:
  A July 18 SIGABRT is retained in the journal. Its stack is an assertion in
  libgvc while changing a PulseAudio card profile:
    _pa_context_set_card_profile_by_index_cb
    pa_context_simple_ack_callback
    g_assertion_message_expr
    abort
  It is related to audio-profile handling, not a pointer/input stack trace.

Do not identify any one of these packages as the QEMU cause without a
controlled host rollback or an upstream match.
